<HEAD>Culture Minister So Many U.S. Shows On French TV Is Humiliating</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Culture Minister <PERSON> Jack </PERSON> <PERSON> Lang </PERSON> says he's sometimes humiliated when he ca n't find anything to watch on the six French television channels but programs imported from the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Lang </PERSON>, in a television interview on Sunday, called on the station chiefs to make their programming `` more French, more European.'' `` I am sometimes humiliated by the fact that at certain times there's nothing to watch but American series,'' he said. `` This is unacceptable. I say to the channel managers: Do your job, serve French culture.'' While <PERSON> Lang </PERSON> was speaking on the state-owned FR3 channel Sunday afternoon, French viewers had the choice of turning to other stations to watch such U.S.-made programs as `` Magnum P.I.,'' `` The Incredible Hulk,'' or `` Max Headroom.''
