<HEAD>Venetian Painting Sells for Record Amount</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VENICE, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A painting by <PERSON> Canaletto </PERSON> has been sold for 1.4 billion lire -LRB- $ 1.01 million -RRB-, a record amount for a Venetian artist's work, the Italian news service <ORGANIZATION> ANSA </ORGANIZATION> reported. The work, called `` The Bull Hunt in St. <PERSON> Mark </PERSON>'s <PERSON> Piazza </PERSON>,'' was sold at an auction Sunday in <LOCATION> Venice </LOCATION>'s <PERSON> Giovannelli </PERSON> Palace. <PERSON> Canaletto </PERSON>, whose real name was <ORGANIZATION> Giovanni </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Antonio </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Canal </ORGANIZATION>, lived from 1697 to 1768 and won fame for his precisely painted views of <LOCATION> Venice </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> and the English countryside. The previous record was not disclosed. <LOCATION> Venice </LOCATION> has a long artistic tradition and has produced such painters as <PERSON> Titian </PERSON>, <PERSON> Paolo </PERSON> <PERSON> Veneziano </PERSON> and <PERSON> Giovanni </PERSON> <PERSON> Bellini </PERSON>.
