<TEXT>
 A chemical spill forced about 1,500 residents to flee their homes for three hours, authorities said. A 55-gallon drum of the insecticide mercapto spilled at <ORGANIZATION> PIE </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trucking </ORGANIZATION> company late Saturday, <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bernardino </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> fire dispatcher <PERSON> Jo </PERSON> <PERSON> Emery </PERSON> said. Authorities could not say how the spill occurred. Residents of a section of this city 50 miles east of <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> were evacuated as a precaution for about three hours, Ms. <PERSON> Emery </PERSON> said. Several people who complained of throat irritation and burning around the mouth were treated at the scene, said Fire Capt. <PERSON> Don </PERSON> <PERSON> Easton </PERSON>. Mercapto can be deadly if ingested or harmful if it comes into direct skin contact, he said.
