RGANIZATION>. Four months later, he was stripped of his citizenship. <PERSON> Lyubimov </PERSON> later became an Israeli citizen. In May, he visited <LOCATION> Moscow </LOCATION> and was given an ovation when he saw a performance at the Taganka of his play about a rebel Soviet poet and singer. He is to return to <LOCATION> Moscow </LOCATION> in January to direct two plays.
