<TEXT>
 Incumbent <PERSON> Ghulam </PERSON> <PERSON> Ishaq </PERSON> <PERSON> Khan </PERSON> easily won a five-year term as <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION>'s president today and Prime Minister <PERSON> Benazir </PERSON> <PERSON> Bhutto </PERSON> scored a victory in her first parliamentary vote of confidence. Federal Election Commissioner <PERSON> S.A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Nusrat </PERSON> said on television that <PERSON> Ishaq </PERSON> <PERSON> Khan </PERSON> swept 78 percent of the presidential vote. Of 446 valid votes, <PERSON> Ishaq </PERSON> <PERSON> Khan </PERSON> polled 348 compared with 91 to his nearest rival, veteran politican <PERSON> Nawabzada </PERSON> <PERSON> Nasrullah </PERSON> <PERSON> Khan </PERSON>, <PERSON> Nusrat </PERSON> said. Ms. <PERSON> Bhutto </PERSON> won her first test of strength in the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Assembly </ORGANIZATION>, the country's lower house of parliament. Of 203 members voting on the confidence motion, 148 said `` yes'' and 55 said `` no.'' Her <ORGANIZATION> Pakistan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> People </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> party emerged as the largest single party Nov. 16 in the country's first free elections in more than a decade. But with 105 seats, it fell short of an outright majority in the 237-seat legislature. The party since gained support from several independents and minor parties. The constitution dictates that the governing party pass a parliamentary test of confidence within 60 days of forming a government. The <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Assembly </ORGANIZATION> and four provincial assemblies functioned as an electoral college for the president. Provincial assemblies were restricted to 45 votes each to put them on equal footing. The populous eastern <LOCATION> Punjab </LOCATION> assembly has 260 members, for example, compared to western <LOCATION> B