</PERSON>, <LOCATION> Indianapolis </LOCATION> Mayor <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Hudnut </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Marion </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> Prosecutor <PERSON> Stephen </PERSON> <PERSON> Goldsmith </PERSON> and Lt. Gov. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Mutz </PERSON>, who was defeated last month in a bid for the governor's office. <PERSON> Orr </PERSON> was moving to fill the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> vacancy before his own term ends early next month, to prevent <LOCATION> Indiana </LOCATION>'s incoming <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> governor, <PERSON> Evan </PERSON> <PERSON> Bayh </PERSON>, from naming a Democrat to the post.
