ow we got out. We tried to find people underneath the rubble but there was so much debris, there was nothing we could do.'' Today's was the third serious rail accident in a month in <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>. On Nov. 30, 15 passengers were injured when two express trains collided outside the <LOCATION> Newcastle-upon-Tyne </LOCATION> in northeast <LOCATION> England </LOCATION>. On Nov. 12, a driver was killed and 18 passengers badly hurt in a crash near <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Helens </LOCATION> in northwest <LOCATION> England </LOCATION>. The ambulance service said today's collision occured at the bottom of an embankment, making it difficult to reach the injured. Some cars overturned, the fire brigade said. The injured were ferried to five hospitals in a fleet of 20 ambulances. British <ORGANIZATION> Rail </ORGANIZATION> said the commuter train was the 7:18 a.m. from <LOCATION> Basingstoke </LOCATION>, southwest of <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>, traveling along the main <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rail </ORGANIZATION> line to <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>'s <LOCATION> Waterloo </LOCATION> station. The second train was the 6:14 a.m. from <LOCATION> Poole </LOCATION>, on <LOCATION> England </LOCATION>'s southern coast, also heading toward <LOCATION> Waterloo </LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rail </ORGANIZATION> said. <ORGANIZATION> Emmanuel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> High </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION> near the scene of the crash was used as a makeshift clinic. Boys from the school scrambled down the banks to help rescue survivors, and elderly people at a nearby day center handed out tea to survivors. <PERSON> Alec </PERSON> <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON>, a school official, said scores of passengers arrived at the school bleeding, dazed and missing teeth. <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>'s worst crash occurred in 1915, when 227 people were killed and 246 injured in a collision between a troop train and passenger train in southwest <LOCATION> Scotland </LOCATION>.
