uch religious legislation as the proposed `` Who Is a Jew'' law, which would accept only conversions to <ORGANIZATION> Judaism </ORGANIZATION> performed by Orthodox rabbis. Jews in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, where the Conservative and Reform movements are strong, oppose the legislation.
