<DATELINE>BATTLE CREEK, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Kellogg </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> said Monday it has stopped using tropical oil in its Cracklin' Oat Bran cereal, eliminating an unwanted dose of saturated fat for consumers who buy the cereal for cholesterol-lowering bran. `` I'm elated,'' said <PERSON> Phil </PERSON> <PERSON> Sokolof </PERSON>, founder of <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Heart </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Savers </ORGANIZATION>, a <LOCATION> Nebraska </LOCATION> organization that has campaigned against products which use tropical oils, such as palm and coconut. `` Thousands of ounces of coconut oil will no longer be clogging the arteries of <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>'' as a result of <PERSON> Kellogg </PERSON>'s action, he said. Oat bran helps keep down cholesterol, while saturated fat can boost it. People who have high levels of cholesterol run a higher risk of a clogging of the arteries that can lead to heart attacks. <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Stewart </PERSON>, senior vice president for <PERSON> Kellogg </PERSON>'s corporate affairs, told <PERSON> Sokolof </PERSON> in a letter that the company was taking coconut oil out of the cereal. He said the new product will be on grocery shelves within three months. <PERSON> Stewart </PERSON> said Monday that <PERSON> Kellogg </PERSON> had been working on a new formula for Cracklin' Oat Bran because the cereal maker sensed growing public sentiment against use of tropical oils. `` We do n't want to lose it -LRB- consumer confidence -RRB- over confusion about one product out of 40,'' he said, adding other Kellogg products do n't contain the tropical oils. <PERSON> Kellogg </PERSON> replaced the coconut oil in Cracklin' Oat Bran with a combination of cottonseed and soybean oils that eliminates the saturated fat content. In addition to <PERSON> Kellogg </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Pepperidge </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Farm </ORGANIZATION> earlier said it was taking tropical oil out