<HEAD>Florio Asks Probe of Navy Computer Contracting</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By TIM AHERN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A key congressman said Monday he wants an investigation into <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION> computer contracts in the wake of a ruling by a federal appeals board that specifications for a series of contracts had favored <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Business </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Machines </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> `` In the next two years, <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> will play an important role in the defense procurement question and with shrinking budgets, it is important that we get the most for our defense dollars,'' said Rep. <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Florio </PERSON>, <PERSON> D-N.J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Florio </PERSON> is chairman of the Energy and Commerce consumer protection subcommittee. Speaking by telephone from his <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> office, <PERSON> Florio </PERSON> said he has asked the <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Accounting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Office </ORGANIZATION> to investigate in the wake of last week's decision by the <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION>'s board of contract appeals The board ruled in a case involving a $ 150 million computer contract. <ORGANIZATION> IBM </ORGANIZATION> competitors had complained, charging that the <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION>'s specifications for the contract unfairly favored the giant company In the ruling, Judge <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> W. </PERSON> <PERSON> Parker </PERSON> concluded that the <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION> contract `` solicitation provides for less than full and open competition and that the <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION> has not properly justified such a restriction on competition.'' Telephone calls seeking comment were not returned Monday by <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION> officials. The case involves a <ORGANIZ