<NOTE>Eds: SUBS NORTHAMPTON, Mass.-dated 1st Item to CORRECT in 8th graf
that characters all named for Renaissance artists, sted painters,
since Donatello was a sculptor; and to CORRECT spelling of
Michelangelo, sted Michaelango, in 9th graf</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NORTHAMPTON, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The creators of Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles, one of the hottest-selling Christmas toys, know what little boys want. `` Kids are into slime,'' said <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Valentine </PERSON>, a toy industry analyst for <ORGANIZATION> Standard </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Poors </ORGANIZATION>. `` Anything to gross out their little sisters.'' The four turtles wielding Ninja weapons have hit No. 11 in the Toy & amp; Hobby World charts of best sellers just four years after they were conceived by <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Laird </PERSON> and <PERSON> Kevin </PERSON> <PERSON> Eastman </PERSON> during a late-evening diet of `` horrible'' television. `` It's insane,'' said <PERSON> Eastman </PERSON>, 26. `` <PERSON> Pete </PERSON> and I really had no idea what we were unleashing. We were just two wild-eyed kids who just wanted to do comic books.'' Eastman, then an occasional student at the <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Massachusetts </ORGANIZATION>, said he tracked down <PERSON> Laird </PERSON>, who scraped out a living by drawing illustrations for local newspapers, in 1982 because their cartoons looked alike. The turtles were created after what <PERSON> Eastman </PERSON> called a heavy dose of `` T.J. Hooker'' and `` Love Boat'' at an apartment the two men shared while <PERSON> Laird </PERSON> was still free-lancing cartoons and Eastman got by making sandwiches at a restaurant. `` We had been watching a bunch of horrible TV and we started drawing and throwing the stuff at each other,'' Eastman said last week. `` We found we had this little beastie that we really fell in love with.'' The beast soon had three brothers, all named after Renaissance artists, and a weird history involving a pool of goo in a <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> sewer and a rat with the powers of a Ninja master. Their creators scraped together $ 1,200 and printed 3,000 copies of the first Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles comic book. The comics sold out in three weeks and <PERSON> Leonardo </PERSON>, <PERSON> Donatello </PERSON>, <PERSON> Michelangelo </PERSON> and <PERSON> Raphael </PERSON> were propelled to fame on T-shirts, cereal boxes and Saturday morning TV. Even avid fan <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Selleck </PERSON> was filmed reading a turtles comic in the farewell episode of `` Magnum, P.I.''
