<HEAD>World Sends Everything From Trained Dogs to Tea for Quake Aid</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Soviet-Quake</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JEFF DONN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 To succor the wretched of <LOCATION> Armenia </LOCATION>'s earthquake, each did what he could Monday: <LOCATION> Alaska </LOCATION> sent dogs to sniff out the trapped, <LOCATION> Kenya </LOCATION> sent tea to warm the chilled, and a <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> millionaire personally delivered a $ 1 million check. Sometimes, their efforts went heartbreakingly awry. Before dawn Monday, a <LOCATION> Yugoslav </LOCATION> military plane crashed while trying to land at <LOCATION> Yerevan </LOCATION> airport with medical supplies. All seven crewmembers aboard were killed, officials said. It was the second crash of a relief aircraft in two days. On Sunday, a Soviet military transport plane went down near <LOCATION> Leninaken </LOCATION>'s airport, killing 78 people Despite Monday's new disaster, <LOCATION> Yugoslavia </LOCATION> was preparing to send another plane soon to help the victims of Wednesday's quake, the official Soviet news agency <ORGANIZATION> Tass </ORGANIZATION> said. In <LOCATION> Juneau </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ala. </LOCATION>, two dogs, their handlers and an official from <LOCATION> Southeast </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Alaska </LOCATION> Dogs Organized for Ground Search planned to take a flight Monday to <LOCATION> Seattle </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Wash. </LOCATION>, pick up doctors and medical supplies there, and fly on to <LOCATION> Armenia </LOCATION>. `` The dogs that are over there are wearing out and they need fresh dogs,'' said Gov. <PERSON> Steve </PERSON> <PERSON> Cowper </PERSON>'s press secretary, <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Ramseur </PERSON>. In <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, officials said <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> private and public donations to Soviet earthquake relief efforts reached $ 3.2 million Monday. First Lady <PERSON> Nancy </PERSON> <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> said she and President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> planned on making their own contribution. The <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATI