Higgins ...'.</NOTE>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY40</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 By the time Marine Lt. Col. <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> R. </PERSON> <PERSON> Higgins </PERSON> left for college, he was well on the way to fulfilling the ambition he expressed in his senior yearbook: `` For my family to always be proud of me.'' His uncle, <PERSON> Delbert </PERSON> <PERSON> Eagle </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Lancaster </LOCATION>, said following <PERSON> Higgins </PERSON>' abduction Feb. 17 in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> that whatever happens, <PERSON> Higgins </PERSON> would continue to make his family and his country proud `` He loves his country,'' <PERSON> Eagle </PERSON> said at the time. `` He is capable of standing up as well as an ordinary man will under the circumstances. ... I do n't think they could bring enough pressure or pain to cause him to betray his country in any way. `` I think he would die first.'' On Monday, Lebanese kidnappers holding <PERSON> Higgins </PERSON>, 43, said in a statement they have sentenced him to death as a spy for <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>. `` We have issued the irrevocable sentence to execute this American spy,'' said the typewritten Arabic statement signed by the Organization of the Oppressed on <LOCATION> Earth </LOCATION>. But the statement did not set an execution date. <PERSON> Higgins </PERSON>' sister, <PERSON> Mary </PERSON> <PERSON> Fisher </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Louisville </LOCATION>, said she had no knowledge of the death threat other than what she has heard from news reports. `` I have not been contacted by anyone,'' she said. <PERSON> Higgins </PERSON> was a onetime aide to former <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> Secretary <PERSON> Caspar </PERSON> <PERSON> Weinberger </PERSON>. When he was abducted, he headed a 75-member observer group assigned to a <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nations </ORGANIZATION> peacekeeping force in south <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>. A <ORGANIZATION> Pentagon </ORGANIZATION> official said at the time of the abduction that <PERS