<HEAD>At The Movies: ``Rain Man,'' ``The Naked Gun''</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 `` Rain Man'' The autistic savant syndrome has been used to describe `` a spectacular skill or talent that occurs in an autistic or retarded child.'' It might seem a likely subject for a disease-of-the-month television movie. Instead, it is the theme of a motion picture, `` Rain Man,'' which is the most original and compelling American drama since `` One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest.'' Yes, it's a drama, though, as in `` Cuckoo,'' there are hearty laughs. Essentially it's the saga of two long-lost brothers seeking a reconciliation against heavy odds. Cruise is a rapacious wheeler-dealer trying to make a bundle by importing sports cars in <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>. His major deal is interrupted by news that his father, from whom he was long estranged, has died in <LOCATION> Cincinnati </LOCATION>. Cruise attends the funeral and learns he has been disinherited. His father's $ 3 million estate has been placed in trust. But for whom? Cruise is astounded to learn that he has an older brother, <PERSON> Hoffman </PERSON>, who has been institutionalized most of his life. Cruise decides to virtually kidnap the brother and fight the will in <LOCATION> California </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Hoffman </PERSON> may seem like an automaton, but he has a superhuman way with numbers. This pays off at the blackjack table in <LOCATION> Las </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Vegas </LOCATION>. That helps ameliorate <PERSON> Cruise </PERSON>'s rage, and he begins to understand and cope with his brother. No good to give away all the plot. Suffice to say that the inspired script by <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> <PERSON> Bass </PERSON> and <PERSON> Barry </PERSON> <PERSON> Morrow </PERSON> -LRB- based on <PERSON> Morrow </PERSON>'s story -RRB- offers a wealth of surprises, both comedic and dramatic <PERSON> Barry </PERSON> <PERSON> Levinson </PERSON> -LRB- `` Tin Men,'' `` Good Morning, <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION>'' -RRB- directs in masterful style. It is his best effort in what promises to be a distinguished career. He maintains a beautiful balance between the hard-driving, cynical Cruise and the childlike <PERSON> Hoffman </PERSON>. <PERSON> Hoffman </PERSON>'s performance is astounding. He gets inside the skin of <PERSON> Raymond </PERSON> <PERSON> Babbitt </PERSON> and never allows him to become monotonous or pitiable. Cruise, dashing in his `` Risky Business'' shades, carries a heavy load, talking at a fast clip as the car dealer and as the exasperated brother struggling to communicate with <PERSON> Raymond </PERSON>. Cruise has emerged as a superb actor as well as teen-age heartthrob. <PERSON> Valerina </PERSON> <PERSON> Golino </PERSON> is excellent as Cruise's understanding girlfriend. <PERSON> Jerry </PERSON> <PERSON> Molen </PERSON> injects humanity into his role as <PERSON> Raymond </PERSON>'s guardian <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> <PERSON> Johnson </PERSON> produced the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Artists </ORGANIZATION> film which is rated R, mostly for Cruise's expletives. Running time: 130 minutes. _ By <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> Writer.
