<TEXT>
 `` The Naked Gun'' When was the last time you had some real fun at a movie? If you have to stop and think, then run, do n't walk, to the nearest theater showing, `` The Naked Gun: From the Files of Police Squad.'' Be prepared for a zany, side-splitting collection of gags _ some of them off color and most of them outrageous. And get ready to give your laugh muscles a workout. `` Naked Gun'' is the latest product of those masters of hilarity, <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Zucker </PERSON>, <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Abrahams </PERSON> and <PERSON> Jerry </PERSON> <PERSON> Zucker </PERSON>, who gave us the memorable `` Airplane!'' and the not-so-memorable `` Top Secret!'' This time they're parodying one of their own failures, the short lived TV series, `` Police Squad!'' Tried and true <PERSON> Leslie </PERSON> <PERSON> Nielsen </PERSON> is back as the unsmiling klutz of the police world, Lt. <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Drebin </PERSON>, who smashes police cars into trash cans, gets his hand stuck in a fish tank and falls over his own feet in the pursuit of justice. He's wonderful. <PERSON> Drebin </PERSON>, trying to foil a plot on the life of Queen <PERSON> Elizabeth </PERSON> <PERSON> II </PERSON>, sets off a series of hilarious non-stop gags. For instance, he winds up as the singer of the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Anthem </ORGANIZATION> and the umpire at a major league baseball game where <PERSON> Reggie </PERSON> <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> plays an unexpected role as assassin-in-waiting. <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Zucker </PERSON>'s direction of these complex sight gags is flawless. <PERSON> Priscilla </PERSON> <PERSON> Presley </PERSON> is <PERSON> Drebin </PERSON>'s romantic interest, <PERSON> Jane </PERSON> <PERSON> Spencer </PERSON>, whose deadpan delivery is a match for <PERSON> Nielsen </PERSON>'s. A scene in which the two practice `` safe sex'' in body size condoms is typical of the giggle power of this film. There is a villain, played by a silky <PERSON> Ricardo </PERSON> <PERSON> Montalban </PERSON>, a bemused sidekick played by <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Kennedy </PERSON> and lots of celebrity cameos as well as a dumpy Queen <PERSON> Elizabeth </PERSON> look-alike. There are no messages here, and the story is just an excuse for some terrific jokes. Call it slapstick. Call it crazy. Call it a hit. `` Naked Gun'' is rated PG-13 for language, double entendres and implied nudity. The very young might wonder why the adults are falling on the floor laughing. _ By <PERSON> Linda </PERSON> <PERSON> Deutsch </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> Writer.
