<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Here is a chronology of the major events of 1988: JAN. 2 _ <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Canada </LOCATION> sign landmark free-trade agreement. JAN. 7 _ Record snowfall in the <LOCATION> South </LOCATION>, record cold across <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> JAN. 28 _ Face-to-face negotiations begin between Contras and <ORGANIZATION> Sandinistas </ORGANIZATION>. Polygamist 13-day siege ends in <LOCATION> Utah </LOCATION>. JAN. 30 _ <ORGANIZATION> Washington </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Redskins </ORGANIZATION> defeat <ORGANIZATION> Denver </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broncos </ORGANIZATION> 42-10 in Super Bowl. FEB. 3 _ Contra aid voted down by House. <PERSON> Anthony </PERSON> <PERSON> Kennedy </PERSON> confirmed as <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> justice. FEB. 8 _ <PERSON> Dole </PERSON> and <PERSON> Gephardt </PERSON> win <LOCATION> Iowa </LOCATION> caucuses. FEB. 13 _ Winter Olympics open in <LOCATION> Calgary </LOCATION>. FEB. 16 _ <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> and <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> win <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hampshire </LOCATION> primary. FEB. 17 _ Marine Lt. Col. <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Higgins </PERSON> kidnapped in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>. FEB. 21 _ <PERSON> Jimmy </PERSON> <PERSON> Swaggart </PERSON> steps down from pulpit in sex scandal. FEB. 23 _ Nationalist protests begin in <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Armenia </LOCATION>. FEB. 25 _ <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION>'s President <PERSON> Delvalle </PERSON> fails in attempt to fire armed forces chief <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>, indicted on drug charges in <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> MARCH 8 _ Super Tuesday: <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> wins 16 of 17 contests, Democratic results split. MARCH 16 _ <PERSON> Poindexter </PERSON>, <LOCATION> North </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Secord </PERSON>, <PERSON> Hakim </PERSON> indicted on conspiracy charges in Iran-Contra affair. MARCH 23 _ <ORGANIZATION> Sandinistas </ORGANIZATION>, Contras sign cease-fire agreement. MARCH 29 _ <PERSON> Dole </PERSON> drops out of presidential race. APRIL 4 _ <ORGANIZATION> Arizona </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> convicts, removes Gov. <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON>. APRIL 16 _ <PERSON> Khalil </PERSON> <PERSON> al-Wazir </PERSON>, senior <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> commander, assassinated in <LOCATION> Tunisia </LOCATION>. APRIL 20 _ Two-week Kuwaiti hijacking ends in <LOCATION> Algiers </LOCATION>. APRIL 26 _ <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> clinches <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> nomination with win in <LOCATION> Pennsylvania </LOCATION>. In South Korean election, government party loses legislative majority to opposition groups. MAY 3 _ Three French hostages released in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>. MAY 4 _ Deadline for illegal aliens in <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> to apply for amnesty. MAY 8 _ <PERSON> Mitterrand </PERSON> re-elected in <LOCATION> France </LOCATION>. MAY 15 _ Soviets begin Afghan troop withdrawal. <LOCATION> Kentucky </LOCATION> school bus collision kills 27. MAY 19 _ Disturbed woman shoots one child dead, wounds five and one adult at <LOCATION> Winnetka </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ill. </LOCATION>, elementary school. MAY 29 _ Reagan-Gorbachev summit begins in <LOCATION> Moscow </LOCATION>. JUNE 7 _ <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> clinches <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> nomination with victories in four primaries. JUNE 13 _ `` Cigarette lawsuit'' in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> decided in favor of plantiff. JUNE 28 _ Opening day of special <ORGANIZATION> Soviet </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> conference that adopts sweeping reforms of Soviet system. JULY 3 _ <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION> cruiser <LOCATION> Vincennes </LOCATION> shoots down <ORGANIZATION> Iran </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> jetliner over <LOCATI