s Soviet president, <PERSON> Gromyko </PERSON> retires. OCT. 3 _ <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION> hostage <PERSON> Mithileshwar </PERSON> <PERSON> Singh </PERSON>, <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> resident, freed. OCT. 5 _ President <PERSON> Pinochet </PERSON> loses Chilean referendum. OCT. 19-25 _ Hurricane <PERSON> Joan </PERSON> kills 111 in <LOCATION> Central </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>. OCT. 20 _ <ORGANIZATION> Dodgers </ORGANIZATION> defeat <ORGANIZATION> Oakland </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> A </ORGANIZATION>'s to win World Series. OCT. 21 _ Deposed Philippine President <PERSON> Ferdinand </PERSON> <PERSON> Marcos </PERSON> and wife, <PERSON> Imelda </PERSON>, indicted on racketeering charges in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. OCT. 26 _ Trapped whales in <LOCATION> Alaskan </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Arctic </LOCATION> freed in combined U.S.-Soviet effort. NOV. 1 _ <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> election, <ORGANIZATION> Likud </ORGANIZATION> gains slightly. NOV. 3 _ Computer virus strikes nationwide research network. NOV. 6 _ Soviet dissident <PERSON> Andrei </PERSON> <PERSON> Sakharov </PERSON> arrives in <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> for visit. NOV. 8 _ <ORGANIZATION> Bush-Quayle </ORGANIZATION> elected. NOV. 15 _ <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> proclaims independent Palestinian homeland. Soviet space shuttle Buran makes first flight, unmanned. NOV. 16 _ In <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Estonia </LOCATION> declares `` sovereignty.'' NOV. 21 _ Conservatives win Canadian election. DEC. 1 _ Supreme Soviet, national parliament, adopts government reforms. DEC. 2 _ Space shuttle <ORGANIZATION> Atlantis </ORGANIZATION> launched on four-day mission; <PERSON> Benazir </PERSON> <PERSON> Bhutto </PERSON> becomes <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION> prime minister. DEC. 5 _ <ORGANIZATION> PTL </ORGANIZATION> founder <PERSON