<HEAD>Japan's Trade Surplus Rises 38 Percent From Year Earlier</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>'s trade surplus continued to rise in November, shooting up 38 percent to $ 6.55 billion from $ 4.75 billion a year earlier, the <ORGANIZATION> Finance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> said Monday. <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>'s surplus with the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> climbed to $ 4.42 billion from $ 4.21 billion a year earlier, the ministry said, reversing 11 straight months of decline. While the overall November surplus was smaller than October's $ 7.69 billion surplus, it surpassed forecasts of a $ 6.5 billion surplus Exports surged 19.5 percent over a year earlier to $ 22.6 billion from $ 18.9 billion, while imports climbed 13.4 percent over a year earlier to $ 16.1 billion from $ 14.2 billion, ministry officials said. The officials predicted that strong export growth `` will continue in the future.''
