<HEAD>Dollar Ends Higher In Europe, Gold Falls</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The dollar rose against major foreign currencies on Monday in <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION> after spending most of the day fluctuating in a narrow range, and gold prices declined. Dealers said there was no particular reason for the dollar's strength on Monday Trading generally was trendless because most market participants were awaiting the release Wednesday of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> trade figures for October, they said. The trade deficit was expected to be little changed in October from September's seasonally adjusted $ 10.4 billion. But a few dealers said they were more bearish, and were looking for a gap between $ 11 billion and $ 12 billion. One dealer said a smaller-than-expected deficit would boost the dollar to its next resistance level at 1.7750 West German marks, while a bearish figure would depress the dollar to the next big support level, which is 1.7150 marks. The dollar rose to 1.7410 marks on Monday from 1.7330 marks on Friday. In <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION>, where trading ends before <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>'s business day begins, the dollar rose 0.49 yen to close at closing 122.92 yen. Later in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>, the dollar was quoted at 122.83 yen. In <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>, the British pound fell to $ 1.8418 from $ 1.8490 on Friday. Other late dollar rates in <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>, compared with late Friday's rates, included: 1.4650 Swiss francs, up from 1.4605; 5.9520 French francs, up from 5.9240; 1.9635 Dutch gu 13:20 12-12 ua PM-Oakdale Dedication, 1st L a0614 0326 13:20 12-12 rw AM-Spotted Owl a0619 0925 13:21 12-12 uw BC-Scotus At-a-Glance a0621 1057 13:24 12-12 ui AM-Quake-Spitak, 1st Ld - Wr a0623 0622 13:26 12-12 ua <ORGANIZATION> AM-Sonja </ORGANIZATION>'s Heart, Bjt a0616 0053 13:26 12-12 ra AM-Rhodes-List, CORRECTIVE a7777 0036 13:27 12-12 rv BC-AP Industry News, <LOCATION> Numberi </LOCATION> a7000 0596 13:28 12-12 rv BC-AP Industry News, Advisor a7001 0769 13:28 12-12 rv BC-AP Industry News, Advi