<HEAD>Japanese Investment Firm Buys 20 Percent Stake in Blackstone Group</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Nikko </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Ltd. </ORGANIZATION>, a Japanese investment giant, has acquired a 20 percent stake in a holding partnership formed by The <ORGANIZATION> Blackstone </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION>, a rapidly-growing investment banking firm, the two concerns said Monday The deal formalizes a business relationship that began when <ORGANIZATION> Nikko </ORGANIZATION> invested $ 100 million in a <ORGANIZATION> Blackstone </ORGANIZATION> buyout fund last year. It gives <ORGANIZATION> Blackstone </ORGANIZATION> an infusion of capital and better access to the Japanese capital markets. It is the latest in a series of alliances that has seen Japanese investment firms buy stakes in the relatively smaller Wall Street investment boutiques that are becoming an increasingly potent force in the mergers and acquisitions arena. Last summer, <ORGANIZATION> Nomura </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> bought a 20 percent stake in the buyout firm <ORGANIZATION> Wasserstein </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> , </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Perella </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, and <ORGANIZATION> Yamaichi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> agreed to buy a 25 percent equity interest in another small buyout firm, <ORGANIZATION> Lodestar </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION>. Tokyo-based <ORGANIZATION> Nikko </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> said it would pay $ 100 million for the interest in the <ORGANIZATION> Blackstone </ORGANIZATION> holding partnership. In exchange, it will be allowed to participate in 20 percent of the profits generated by <ORGANIZATION> Blackstone </ORGANIZATION>'s financial advisory activities and its investment banking affiliates, such as <ORGANIZATION> Blackstone </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Financial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Management </ORGANIZATION> which oversees investments in two mutual funds. The agreement `` formalizes a basis for close cooperation on U.S.-Japan M & amp; A transactions between the two firms,'' the statement said. <ORGANIZATION> Blackstone </ORGANIZATION> was founded three years ago and is headed by <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> G. </PERSON> <PERSON> Peterson </PERSON>, the former <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION> secretary and onetime chairman of <ORGANIZATION> Lehman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Brothers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kuhn </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Loeb </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> which has become part of <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lehman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hutton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc </ORGANIZATION>. Among its six general partners is <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Stockman </PERSON>, the former director of the <ORGANIZATION> Office </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Management </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Budget </ORGANIZATION> under President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON>. In October 1987, <ORGANIZATION> Nikko </ORGANIZATION> paid $ 100 million to become one of three limited partner-investors in <ORGANIZATION> Blackstone </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Capital </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Blackstone </ORGANIZATION>'s buyout fund that currently has more than $ 750 million of equity capital. The fund's biggest deals to date include the $ 2.6 billion buyout of <ORGANIZATION> Wickes </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> and its $ 600 million purchase of 51 percent of <ORGANIZATION> USX </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>'s transportation subsidiaries which it operates in partnership with <ORGANIZATION> USX </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Blackstone </ORGANIZATION> also has advised on merger and aquisition deals valued at more than $ 15 billion, including <ORGANIZATION> Sony </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>'s $ 2 billion purchase of <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Records </ORGANIZATION> and the acquisition of <ORGANIZATION> Firestone </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tire </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Rubber </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> by <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Bridgestone </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> `` We have been pleased and impressed with <ORGANIZATION> Blackstone </ORGANIZATION>'s performance and basic philosophy,'' said <PERSON> Yasuo </PERSON> <PERSON> Kanzaki </PERSON>, executive vice president of <ORGANIZATION> Nikko </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> He said <PERSON> Nikko </PERSON> and the `` vast majority of Japanese corporations share <ORGANIZATION> Blackstone </ORGANIZATION>'s strictly friendly philosophy in both its advisory and principal actvities.'' <ORGANIZATION> Nikko </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> is one of the biggest Japanese investment houses with $ 4.7 billion in capital as of September 1988. <PERSON> Peterson </PERSON>, who is chairman of <ORGANIZATION> Blackstone </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION>, and <PERSON> Stephen </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Schwarzman </PERSON>, president, said in a joint statement that the investment by <PERSON> Nikko </PERSON> would help <ORGANIZATION> Blackstone </ORGANIZATION> finance its diversification plans into areas such as the restructuring of troubled companies, obtain better access to the Japanese capital markets and provide better service to its existing clients. `` Finally it provides all these benefits while permitting us the freedom to continue to operate out business in the way we have,'' the statement said.
