<HEAD>Chevron Announces $100 Million Loss on Irving Oil Sale</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> announced Monday it will post a loss in excess of $ 100 million after taxes in the fourth quarter on the sale of its 48.9 percent stake in <ORGANIZATION> Irving </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ltd </ORGANIZATION>. But a spokesman for the oil giant said the charge should not result in a net loss for the quarter. <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION> said it sold its interest in <ORGANIZATION> Irving </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> on Friday after having an interest in the firm for more than 30 years, said <PERSON> Steve </PERSON> <PERSON> McLennan </PERSON>, manager of investor relations for <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION> would not disclose the details of the transaction. <PERSON> Irving </PERSON> <PERSON> Oil </PERSON> is a privately-held company based in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Brunswick </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Canada </LOCATION>, that operates a refinery and has a number of marketing outlets. <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION> officials denied that the sale, which had been negotiated `` for some time,'' was prompted by anything in particular. `` It's been a profitable enterprise for us,'' he said. `` The charge we're taking in the fourth quarter is, in a sense, undoing a little bit of the profits of the past. Overall, it's been a profitable investment.'' <PERSON> McLennan </PERSON> said it `` was in neither one of our interests'' to continue the minority interest. The two companies have some `` very, very small'' joint operations that will continue under contract, he added. `` Although it is a substantial loss to take, it should not put us in the red for the quarter,'' said <PERSON> McLennan </PERSON>. `` It should n't really even come close.'' <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION> had net income of $ 220 million, or 64 cents a share, in the foureth quarter a year ago after taking a charge of $ 93 million related to the disposition and write-off of assets. In trading on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION> rose 12 -LCB- cents a share to $ 46 on Monday.
